{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Northern Cyprus", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox outbreak\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus\n| map1 = \n| legend1 = \n| map2 = \n| legend2 = \n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus]]\n| first_case = [[Nicosia]]\n| arrival_date = 10 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=10|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| first_outbreak = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases = 44<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kibrisgazetesi.com/kibris/kktcde-bir-kiside-daha-koronavirus-vakasi-h85865.html|title=KKTC'de bir ki\u015fide daha Koronavir\u00fcs vakas\u0131!|website=kibrisgazetesi.com|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n| deaths = 3<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tr.euronews.com/2020/03/28/kktc-de-koronavirus-nedeniyle-ilk-olum|title=KKTC'de koronavir\u00fcs nedeniyle ilk \u00f6l\u00fcm|date=28 March 2020|website=euronews|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/dunya/kktcde-korona-virusten-2-olum-41483719|title=KKTC'de Korona vir\u00fcsten 2. \u00f6l\u00fcm|website=www.hurriyet.com.tr|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 100\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili = \n| website = \n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Northern Cyprus]], officially the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus (the Turkish-Cypriot-controlled ''[[de facto]]'' state comprising the north of the island), in March 2020.\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{expand section|date=April 2020}}\n\n=== March 2020 ===\nOn 10 March 2020, Health Minister [[Ali Pilli]] announced the Northern Cyprus's first case of [[COVID-19]], a 65-year-old tourist from [[Germany]].<ref name=\"First\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/10/german-tourist-tests-positive-for-virus-in-northern-cyprus-.html |title=German tourist tests positive for virus in Northern Cyprus |date=13 March 2020 |via=athejakartapost}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, the country's second case was confirmed, being the spouse of the German tourist who became the first person diagnosed with COVID-19.<ref name=\"Case_2\">{{Cite web |url=https://ahvalnews.com/coronavirus/second-coronavirus-case-northern-cyprus |title=Second coronavirus case in northern Cyprus |date=13 March 2020 |via=aa.com.tr}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus (TRNC) announced that five people have been tested positive for the coronavirus, up from two.<ref name=\"Case_5\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/northern-cyprus-confirms-total-of-5-coronavirus-cases/1764711 |title=Northern Cyprus confirms total of 5 coronavirus cases |date=13 March 2020 |via=aa.com.tr}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, the [[2020 Northern Cypriot presidential election]] was delayed for 6 months due to the outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnturk.com/turkiye/kktcde-cumhurbaskanligi-secimleri-6-ay-erteleniyor|title=KKTC'de Cumhurba\u015fkanl\u0131\u011f\u0131 se\u00e7imleri 6 ay erteleniyor|website=CNN T\u00fcrk|language=tr|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, over 840 [[Germans|German]] national tourists were sent back to [[Germany]] after being quarantined for 14 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/avrupa/kktcde-karantinadaki-almanlar-ulkelerine-donuyor-41476774|title=KKTC'de karantinadaki Almanlar \u00fclkelerine d\u00f6n\u00fcyor|first=Sefa KARAHASAN|last=DHA|website=www.hurriyet.com.tr|accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the first person died from COVID-19.\n\n=== April 2020 ===\nNorth Cyprus announced partial curfew until 10 April. The exception is just for using markets and other mandatory needs. Moreover, fully curfew is under action within the 9pm to 6am until 10 April.\n\n15 villages within the \u0130skele/Karpaz district is under application of the fully curfew due to high number of cases.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/turkish-cyprus-declares-curfew-153448 |title=Turkish Cyprus declares curfew |website=Hurriyet Daily News |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nTurkish Cypriot authorities banned movement between districts, meaning no one will be allowed to travel from one district to another.\n\nThree students of 800 who came from UK were under self isolated quarantine for 14 days, have tested positive.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kibrisgazetesi.com/corona-virus/kktc-de-koronavirus-vaka-sayisi-91-oldu-h86514.html|title=KKTC'de Koronavir\u00fcs vaka say\u0131s\u0131 91 oldu|website=kibrisgazetesi.com}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Day !! New cases !! Cumulative cases\n|-\n| {{dts|10 March 2020}} || 1 || 1\n|-\n| {{dts|12 March 2020}} || 1 || 2\n|-\n| {{dts|13 March 2020}} || 3 || 5\n|-\n| {{dts|14 March 2020}} || 0 || 5\n|-\n| {{dts|15 March 2020}} || 1 || 6\n|-\n| {{dts|16 March 2020}}|| 1 || 7\n|-\n| {{dts|17 March 2020}} || 13 || 20\n|-\n| {{dts|18 March 2020}} || 0 ||  20\n|-\n| {{dts|19 March 2020}} || 13 || 33<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/koronavirus/kktcde-kovid-19-vaka-sayisi-33e-yukseldi/1772461|